Jason B Kieffer

Burial Date September 5, 2008

Obituary Viewed 1546 times

Posted by:

Reid Pulley

Awesome teammate, roommate, lifting partner, student, friend, and a brother to us all.;

Posted by:

Tom and Betty Kieffer

When the Lord calls our loved ones home, he leaves a gift of memories in exchange. Know that we have many happy ones of Jason. All our love.;

Posted by:

Alexander Escobar

To the Kieffer Family, I did not know Jason long, but was fotunate to have worked with him when he joined Dart. Jason was a very warm, extremely personable young man and I feel honored to have shared a beer with him on his birthday. Having lost two close cousins at the young ages of 23 and 24, my most heartfelt condolences go out to you on the early loss of your son, brother, friend.;

Posted by:

Sean McCall

My deepest condolences to everyone who knew and loved Jason. He was a lovely man who always had a smile on his face. He will be forgotten by few and missed by many.;

Posted by:

Sylvia B. Dobrovolny

Dearest Kathy and Family, During this time of profound grief in your lives, my prayer is that your faith in our loving Savior will uphold you and bring peace to your hearts. May the happy times that you spent with your dear son and brother provide memories that will strengthen you to face the days ahead. I am deeply sorry for your loss. With Loving Sympathy, Sylvia Dobrovolny;

Posted by:

Robin Kieffer

Jason was a gentle soul who will be greatly missed by all of us. Please know that we all share your sorrow too deep for words. My prayers and love are with you.;

Posted by:

Lindsay Kieffer

"Work hard....play harder.....words that I try to live by. Definitely feel that you gotta try things at least once and live life with an open mind and an open spirit" Those were Jason's own words about himself and they are very true. Our lives are better because he was a part of them.;

Posted by:

Alicia Orvik

Jason was a gentle soul that I and many others will never forget. My thoughts a prayers are with family and friends at this time of sorrow.;

Posted by:

Donna Quinlan

Hearts are breaking for your loss. So many warm thoughts are with you today and through the days that come and go. Sending heartfelt sympathy to your family and friends. Love and Prayers Donna Quinlan;

Posted by:

Sylvia Reuter Sultenfuss

I sense the deep pain and shock at your loss and can only imagine how you must be walking this journey. I am sending light and lots of love to surround you in grace and healing. love...sylvia;

Posted by:

Tom and Juline Zehoski

Tom and I want to tell you how terribly, terribly sorry we are over your loss. Our hearts are broken for you. If only we could turn back time..... Our love and prayers. Tom and Juline Zehoski;

Posted by:

Randy and Kathy Barabas

We are praying every day that God's mercy will bring you comfort. He promises that you will be reunited with Jason to spend eternity "together".;

Posted by:

Craig Frommelt

I cannot possibly express the sorrow I feel over this tragic event. Hopefully faith in a bigger plan and a higher meaning to all things will help the family make it through these trying times.;

Posted by:

Leo and Martha Ellingson

Although we did not know Jason....as extended family we send our deepest sympathy to the Kieffer family. May God Bless you in this difficult time.;

Posted by:

Brett Legler

Keep swinging for the fences on your new team. You'll be missed but not forgotten.;

Posted by:

Valerie Bowe

Terry and family, Please accept my deepest condolences on the loss of your son. My thoughts and prayers are with you at this difficult time. Take care, Valerie Bowe;

Posted by:

Heidi Lindberg

Jason was a great and true friend to all he came in contact with. I have no doubt he is residing with the lord and is now a guardian angel to many. He will be missed, Heidi;

Posted by:

Mahlon and Jean Randall

Terry and Family, Our thoughts and prayers are with you at this sad time, as our those of your many Unisys associates.;

Posted by:

David and Micki Westbrook

Words cannot even begin to express our sorrow. May the memories of Jason give you strength and knowing an Angel is watching over you give you comfort. You are in our Prayers. God's Peace.;

Posted by:

Brian J. Gowling

Jason, I will always remember our times spent playing traveling baseball; fishing up on Lake Wabana for the bass opener; carpooling to the Zoo School; and your numerous visits to Madison for Halloween. I am very glad I got to catch up with you a few weeks ago at my house. You've always been like a brother to me. You will always be remembered. Kief, LL, Just Kickin' It. I love you and will always cherish the memories we had. Love, Brian;

Posted by:

David Berthiaume

Dear Kieffer family, Jason and your family are in the Berthiaume family's prayers. I had the pleasure of playing fastpitch softball with Jason over 3 years and will truly miss Jason as a teammate but mostly as a friend. May Jason's soul rest in peace, Amen.;

Posted by:

Mike Munyon

Kathy & Terry, Jason - what a neat kid. Words can't begin to describe how sad I am right now. My thoughts and prayers are with all of you.;

Posted by:

Kevin Kammueller

My condolences, and those of all my teammates with the Jordan Realty fastpitch team, go out to the family and friends of Jason. The softball community has lost another special player long before his time. He will truly be missed.;

Posted by:

Kathryn Atterberry

Jenny, Mason and family, Words cannot express how sorry we are for your tremendous loss. Chris and I remember Jason as such a happy and warm guy. You could tell how much he loved his family and friends. Thinking of you, Chris & Kathryn Atterberry;

Posted by:

Bryan Hins

Many of these messages tell Jason's story... an upbeat lovable personality. He obviously touched many people and made their lives so much better. My thoughts and prayers go out to your family in this difficult time.;

Posted by:

Jennifer Zurick

Dear Kieffer family, Our thoughts and prayers are with you during this heartbreaking time. We liked Jason so much and I used to think, "well, he's single and our Katie is single - maybe they'll meet up some time." He was that special of a guy! We just saw him at Gowlings and he was so happy, and as usual, was so quick with a hug. He will be missed by so many people! Our deepest sympathy is being sent your way.;

Posted by:

Aaron S. Vail

The softball world lost one of its own. We will miss your genuineness, sincerity, and smile. You were a great teammate, player, and person. The Pirates will miss their leader and their friend. Rest in Peace Puck.;

Posted by:

Mike and Abra Hovgaard

Kieffer Family, We are so saddened to hear about your loss. We are keeping you in our thoughts and prayers. God bless you, Mike, Abra, Cindy, and Jessie Hovgaard;

Posted by:

Emily Cunningham

Dear Jenny and Family, My thoughts and prayers are with you! May god give you the strength during this difficult time. With Deepest sympathy Emily Cunningham;

Posted by:

Gail Dorsey

Dear Kieffer Family, We will never forget the trip that Sean, Jason & others took to Colorado when their van broke down (losing a tire) and our late night worried phone calls to you about their whereabouts. Our family has many fond summer memories of Sean and Luke playing baseball with Jason - it seems like just yesterday that they were out there tossing the ball around. May the wonderful memories you shared together as a family comfort you through this very difficult time. We will be keeping you all in our thoughts and prayers. Mike & Gail Dorsey;

Posted by:

Stacy

Terry, Kathy, and Jenny, I am so very sorry for your loss. I have many fond memories of growing up with Jason and the Kieffer's at the Friday night games. Also lots of memories of "kids games" at "Quadna" each year. You will all be in my thoughts and prayers through this very difficult time. Love, Stacy Zachman;

Posted by:

Tiffany (Foster) Johnson

Terry, Kathy and Jenny, I am so saddend by the passing of Jason. I can't beleive this has happened to such a sweet and handsome man. I remeber babysitting him when I was around 8 or 9 years old. It was always a treat to see Jason and Jenny for one of my many times babaysitting for you. We always had such fun times during those days. I couldn't beleive how he was going to college and studying on COPD and other lung problems and how my dad (Tom Foster) wanted him to find a cure so no one else would have to have such a horrible thing. When I heard the news, I didn't know what to say but that I am so sorry for the loss of Jason. I wish I was there to help comfort all of you, like you were here for me when my dad passed 5 years ago. I miss and love all of you and please know that I am with you on this sad occation.;

Posted by:

Jessie Hetland

My thoughts and my prayers are with you!;

Posted by:

Pete Korchik

Jenny, Mason, family, and friends Jason's enthusiasm could be so contagious. He was able to enrich so many peoplesÃ¢?(TM) lives. He has given me memories that will forever make me smile and laugh. My thoughts are with you all. Thinking of you, Pete;

Posted by:

Jen and Darren Anderson

Jenny, Mason & family- We are so sorry to hear of the sudden passing of Jason. He will be missed by all of us. We are thinking of you at this very difficult time.;

Posted by:

Tom and Jan Hetland

Dear Terry, Kathy and Jenny, We would like to express our deepest sympathy for the loss of your beloved Jason. We are praying for you and all of your family members. We didn't know Jason all that well, but we do remember he was such an outstanding and kind person with a personality that would light up a room. Our thoughts and prayers are with you!;

Posted by:

Thomas Penshorn

Jason was a good kid. I'll miss golfing and the random moments I spent with him though friends. He was always a great guy to hang out with, and was easy to get to know. You will be missed Kieffer!!!;

Posted by:

Gerardo Pedra

My heartfelt condolences to you and your family. May God give you all the courage and strength to tide over this loss. May the departed soul rest in peace. A big hug from MÃÂ©xico;

Posted by:

Lowery Abel

I worked with Jason for three days in January while he was training for Dart. I enjoyed my time with him in Mineapolis and was looking forward to reconnecting with him in Vancouver in September. I'm so sorry for your loss. May God comfort you.;

Posted by:

Penny Swenson

Terry, Kathy, Jenny, and Mason, The love for Jason will never end and the memories will never go away. May god hold you close now and in the days to come. Jason brought joy to scores of people! He loved his family and god with all of his heart. He will be missed. You are in our hearts and prayers, Lance and Penny;

Posted by:

Meg Lustig

Terry, Jason was a gift to you, your family and friends. Revel in the joy he brought you. Celebrate him! With love, Meg;

Posted by:

Chris Kuhn

Jason was so full of life. He had a great sense of humor and I always appreciated the attention and focus he gave to me whenever I saw him. He took a lot of nickels, dimes, and quarters off me in poker. I'll never forget the time he was over for a social gathering and I introduced him to his own cousin. May he celebrate with all the angels and saints in God's presence. And for those of us who miss him and his loving family may God grant us peace until we are reunited.;

Posted by:

Frank and Vanessa Cossetta

The Kieffer Family-I just want to let you know how very saddened I am to hear about the passing of Jason. He was such a kind, gentle soul and would do anything to help someone in need. I know how difficult this must be for you. You are in my thoughts and prayers. "Perhaps they are not stars, but rather openings in Heaven where the love of our lost ones pours through and shines down upon us to let us know that they are happy" With love and hugs, Vanessa;

Posted by:

Eric Swenson and Jenni Groetsc

Terry, Kathy, Jenny and Mason, Our thoughts and prayers are with you. May your faith raise you up and give you the strength to get through this incredibly hard time. Much Love, Eric & Jenni;

Posted by:

Eliseo Subranni and Michelle C

Dear Kieffer Family, I met Jason through a training session we had together at Dart. I am deeply sadened and emotional to hear of the passing of such a young person. I wish to extend my deepest condolences for your loss.;

Posted by:

Kim Seivert

I was deeply saddened to hear of your loss. May the peace which comes from the memories of love shared, comfort you now and in the days ahead. I knew Jason through a friend. All of my memories of Jason are of his contagious smile. He was great guy, I'm glad to have known him. He will be missed.;

Posted by:

Lindsey (Haberman) Hamilton

Dear Kieffer family, I went to high school with Jason and he was such a joy to be around. I have many good memories of him. I am saddened to hear about the loss of Jason. My prayers and thoughts are with you all. May your faith keep you strong during this tough time.;

Posted by:

Jeff Ochs

I lived two doors down from Jason. He offered me a beer not more than two weeks ago. I am shocked and saddened by his passing. I won't be able to attend the services, as I am out of town on work. However, I send my regards to his family.;

Posted by:

Kerstin Balli

I can't begin to tell you how sorry I am for your loss. My heart goes out to the Kieffer family.;

Posted by:

Mullins, Terry and Cathy

Terry, Kathy, & Jenny, We are very fortunate and honored to have had Jason in our lives. He was a warm, welcoming person, very kind, caring and loving, with such a gentleness about him...and the world's best hugger! We all are experiencing such deep pain and tremendous sympathy for the loss of your child, and Jenny your brother, our nephew, and our children's cousin. You are in our thoughts and prayers. A plan of much greater magnitude is in place for Jason! Love, Terry & Cathy Mullins
